{"title":"Cobalt Bikes takes off with new custom titanium mountain and gravel bikes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/cobalt-bikes-takes-off-with-new-custom-titanium-mountain-and-gravel-bikes/","date":1638804619000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags-.jpeg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti Warhawk with bags\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151409/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-with-bags-.jpeg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280006\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Cobalt bikes, (primarily a carbon bike manufacturer) are now offering their Warhawk gravel and Diablo mountain frames with a custom titanium spin.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti DiabloBB\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151356/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-DiabloBB-768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><p>The Cobalt brand started with carbon but now is turning some of its time to custom titanium bikes. The all-new Ti-WarHawk and Ti-Diablo are offered in the same geometry as the carbon versions but have some super cool upgrades.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti Warhawk internal cable\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable-.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151403/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-internal-cable--768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><p>Those looking to customize their titanium frame can do so quickly, with no added price to the frame purchase.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti Warhawk TT\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151406/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-TT-768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><h2>How custom are we talking about?</h2><p>Riders can change the seat or head tube angles from the base geometry and the seat tube and top tube lengths depending on preference. The baseline geometry for both the WarHawk and Diablo isnâ€™t anything outrageous, but riders with specific needs can take advantage of customizations.</p><h2>Cobalt Warhawk Geometry</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes WarHawk Geo\" width=\"1280\" height=\"890\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo-297x207.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo-800x556.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo-120x83.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151945/Cobalt-Bikes-WarHawk-Geo-768x534.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><h2>Cobalt Diablo MTB Geometry</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes MTB geo\" width=\"1280\" height=\"802\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo-297x186.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo-800x501.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo-120x75.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151934/Cobalt-Bikes-MTB-geo-768x481.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><p>Other custom options include; cable routing (internal or external) for shifting/dropper post and bottle cage mounts/accessory mount locations.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti Warhawk BB\" width=\"960\" height=\"1280\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB-.jpeg 960w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB--225x300.jpeg 225w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB--800x1067.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB--90x120.jpeg 90w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151400/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Warhawk-BB--768x1024.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"></a></p><p>The default bottom bracket style is threaded T47, but those with other needs can choose BSA, press-fit BB86, or BB92 (MTB).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti diablo\" width=\"1280\" height=\"761\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo-297x177.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo-800x476.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo-120x71.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151938/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-diablo-768x457.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><h3>Pricing and availability</h3><ul><li>Cobalt Warhawk Titanium frame (full carbon fork included) $2,199.00</li><li>Cobalt Diablo Titanium frame $2,199.00</li></ul><p>Those looking to order a ti-custom Cobalt can do so from the Cobalt site, 50% deposit is due with the frame order, and lead time is 45-60 days.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame-.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cobalt Bikes Ti Diablo FrameCobalt Bikes Ti Diablo Frame\" width=\"1280\" height=\"960\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame-.jpeg 1280w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/03151353/Cobalt-Bikes-Ti-Diablo-Frame--768x576.jpeg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px\"></a></p><p>Each frame is available with a custom build of the riderâ€™s choosing, ranging from Shimano GRX to SRAM AXS â€” the build possibilities are wide and Cobalt works with many component brands.</p><p><em><a href=\"https://cobaltbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">cobaltbike.com</a></em></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"18a86c09f682374885e968b99956a1c9cad3c2b36da7e970e1b3945e86289d17","category":"Cycling"}